<section
	id="faq"
	class="py-14 sm:py-16 border-t border-slate-200/70 bg-white"
	aria-labelledby="faq-heading"
>
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div
			class="grid lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.1fr),minmax(0,1fr)] gap-10 items-start"
		>
			<div>
				<h2
					id="faq-heading"
					class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900"
				>
					Answers to questions SMEs actually ask.
				</h2>
				<p class="mt-3 text-base text-slate-600 max-w-2xl">
					peppol.taxera.tech is intentionally narrow in scope:
					outbound PEPPOL e‑invoices for Swiss SMEs, built on Taxera’s
					enterprise infrastructure. Here’s what that means in
					practice.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
				<!-- FAQ items -->
				<details
					class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 open:bg-slate-50"
					open
				>
					<summary
						class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-3 text-slate-900 font-semibold list-none"
					>
						<span>
							Do I need an ERP system to use peppol.taxera.tech?
						</span>
						<span
							class="flex h-6 w-6 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-300 text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-90 transition-transform"
							aria-hidden="true"
						>
							<i
								class="lucide lucide-chevron-right text-xs"
								style="stroke-width:1.5"></i>
						</span>
					</summary>
					<p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-600">
						No. The portal is designed specifically for SMEs without
						a PEPPOL‑enabled ERP. You work directly in the browser:
						configure your company profile, enter invoices manually
						or upload files (depending on plan), and track status in
						the dashboard.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details
					class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4"
				>
					<summary
						class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-3 text-slate-900 font-semibold list-none"
					>
						<span>
							Which countries can I send PEPPOL invoices to?
						</span>
						<span
							class="flex h-6 w-6 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-300 text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-90 transition-transform"
							aria-hidden="true"
						>
							<i
								class="lucide lucide-chevron-right text-xs"
								style="stroke-width:1.5"></i>
						</span>
					</summary>
					<p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-600">
						The underlying Taxera access point connects to the
						global PEPPOL network. As long as your customer is
						registered in PEPPOL and the profile is supported, the
						portal will route your invoice accordingly. Exact
						country and profile support will be listed in the live
						documentation.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details
					class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4"
				>
					<summary
						class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-3 text-slate-900 font-semibold list-none"
					>
						<span>How are failed invoices handled?</span>
						<span
							class="flex h-6 w-6 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-300 text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-90 transition-transform"
							aria-hidden="true"
						>
							<i
								class="lucide lucide-chevron-right text-xs"
								style="stroke-width:1.5"></i>
						</span>
					</summary>
					<p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-600">
						Technical and business‑rule errors are surfaced in the
						portal with clear messages. In addition, Taxera’s
						internal console allows staff to review logs and, where
						appropriate, manually reprocess affected invoices.
						Customers never see internal tooling – only concise,
						actionable status updates.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details
					class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4"
				>
					<summary
						class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-3 text-slate-900 font-semibold list-none"
					>
						<span>
							What happens if I exceed my monthly invoice limit?
						</span>
						<span
							class="flex h-6 w-6 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-300 text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-90 transition-transform"
							aria-hidden="true"
						>
							<i
								class="lucide lucide-chevron-right text-xs"
								style="stroke-width:1.5"></i>
						</span>
					</summary>
					<p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-600">
						The dashboard shows real‑time usage against your plan
						limit. Close to the limit, you’ll see prompts to
						upgrade. Final behavior (soft overage vs. strict cap)
						will be defined in the portal’s terms; in all cases,
						you’ll see clear messaging before any blocking changes
						take effect.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details
					class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4"
				>
					<summary
						class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-3 text-slate-900 font-semibold list-none"
					>
						<span>
							How are payments and cancellations managed?
						</span>
						<span
							class="flex h-6 w-6 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-300 text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-90 transition-transform"
							aria-hidden="true"
						>
							<i
								class="lucide lucide-chevron-right text-xs"
								style="stroke-width:1.5"></i>
						</span>
					</summary>
					<p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-600">
						Subscriptions renew monthly via a Swiss payment
						provider. You can cancel or change your plan in the
						portal, with changes applying to the next billing
						period. Failed payments trigger reminders and, if
						unresolved, an automatic suspension that you can lift by
						updating payment details.
					</p>
				</details>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
